Got the following NPE:

java.lang.NullPointerException
  at
org.eclipse.osgi.framework.adaptor.core.BundleEntry$ZipBundleEntry.getFileURL(BundleEntry.java:154)

Here is the relevant code:

public URL getFileURL() {
  try {
    File file = bundleFile.getFile(zipEntry.getName());
    return file.toURL(); // << NPE happens here
  } catch (MalformedURLException e) {
    //This can not happen. 
    return null;
  }
}

Basically, it is not prepared to handle the case where BundleFile#getFile will
return null. That is possible. In my scenario, the file (a JAR file inside a
JAR'd bundle) could not be extracted because I was running with the
configuration area in read only mode. It is true that that would fail later
anyway, but the NPE makes the problem hard to diagnose.

The fix seems simple (make sure all clients of BundleFie#getFile handle null),
and I believe we should fix it for M7.
